Title: A Sparse Representation for Function Approximation  
Author: Tomaso Poggio and Federico Girosi 
Address: Cambridge MA 02139 USA  
Affiliation: Center for Biological and Computational Learning and Artificial Intelligence Laboratory Massachusetts Institute of Technology  
Abstract: We derive a new general representation for a function as a linear combination of local correlation kernels at optimal sparse locations (and scales) and characterize its relation to PCA, regularization, sparsity principles and Support Vector Machines. 
